JOHANNESBURG – De Beers will now be selling manufactured diamonds. The world’s biggest diamond miner announced this week it will be launching a new jewellery brand, featuring gemstones grown in the lab. READ: De Beers returns to roots with Kimberley exploration drive The group is investing over R1-trillion on a production facility over the next four years to produce these diamonds. It says this will offer consumers high quality fashion jewellery at a more affordable price. The lab-grown diamonds will cost around R10,000 per carat to be sold from September under its new brand, Lightbox Jewelry. eNCA